    "title": "build: Evaluate passing depend's build_{CC,{C,CPP,LD}FLAGS} to bitcoin's configure",
    "body": "`secp256k1` uses the native toolchain to do its ecmult static precomputation. Since depends users can specify their \"build\" (native) toolchain, we should put that in the resulting `config.site` so that bitcoin's configure can pick it up and pass it to `secp256k1` as `{CC,{C,CPP,LD}FLAGS}_FOR_BUILD` variables. Consistency FTW!",
